cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with facial geometry reconstruction from images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), but since the focus is on computer vision, cs.CV is more likely. The paper also deals with geometric structures and facial correspondence maps, which are topics in computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of neural networks for image-to-image translation also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the use of synthetic data and evaluation on in-the-wild facial images, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
